The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, April 18 (PTI): Police today questioned the school teacher accused in the death of Shanno, a Class II student in a municipal school in north Delhi.           
	The 11-year-old student died yesterday after she was reportedly made to stand in the sun for hours by class teacher Manju on Wednesday as she failed to translate a word into English. The initial post-mortem did not reveal any injury mark on Shannos body.                   
	 Mumbai: Foreign experts, including those from Americas Federal Bureau of Investigation, will be among the 109 witnesses the prosecution will examine in the Mumbai attack case involving Ajmal Kasab. They will be examined on the evidence collected from Global Positioning Systems and mobile phones used by the 10-member terror module.                   
	 Lucknow: Maneka Gandhi has filed her nomination from Aonla near Bareilly. Maneka, as her affidavit said, has assets worth over Rs 15 crore and gold jewellery of Rs 41 lakh. Her son Varun, out on a two-week parole in a hate speech case, has requested the Election Commission to appoint neutral observers and videograph the proceedings when he files his nomination in Pilibhit on April 22 as he apprehends mischief by the Uttar Pradesh government.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): Shashi Tharoor, the Congress candidate in Thiruvananthapuram, was granted bail on Saturday in a case of alleged disrespect to the national anthem. Tharoor later claimed the allegation was a lie.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): Two militants have been killed and a girl injured during an encounter with security forces in Doda district. The rebels opened fire when the troops asked them to surrender.                                                                                                                           
